txt.en: 'Beset from the north - beset from the south - they clamp down on us like wolven jaws!'
'We retreat into the marshes. Pray some host of Elves or Men come - come soon!'
'Fight, my kin, fight now or all is lost!'
'The din of war is like no other - Orcs shrieking, steel clanging.'
'Look how they yield before us! We shall pursue them to the Black Gates. We shall-'
'Ugh! What? I am slain in the hour of victory. O woe!'
'Those are no birds - they are Orkish arrows! O Elbereth! Nowhere to run.'
'So this is death. I never thought...'
'How easy it must be for Men, all doomed to this.'
'How hard... the pain... sweet life, farewell...'
